    "6 -UNESCO (2022): Recommendation on the Ethics of Artificial Intelligence (SHS/BIO/PI/2021/1).",
    "7 -OECD (2019): Recommendation of the Council on Artificial Intelligence (OECD/LEGAL/0449). 8",
    "The ethical dilemmas established by these international documents (most of which is considered soft law material) were then used to inductively identify the primary aspects around which the investigation of educational AI principles may be organised.",
    "Among the above documents, the EUHLEX material is the salient one as it contains a Glossary that defines and explains, among others, the two primary concepts that will be used in this paper: \"artificial intelligence\" and \"ethics\".",
    "As this paper is, to a large extent, based on the deducted categorisation embedded in these international documents, it will follow suit in using the above terms as EUHLEX did, supporting it with the definitions contained in the other four referenced international documents."
